g.text: KMRR found lower covariance between paralog expression than
orthologs expression. This was interpretted to indicate more change
in expression following duplication than speciation, and as support
We reanalyzed the KMRR study with independent contrasts, which
isolate changes following duplication and speciation and do not
count changes along the same branches multiple times. These
reanalyses do not reject the null that the rate of change in expression
following duplication is the same as that after speciation (Wilcoxon p=1).
